Second Lady Karen Pence recently visited Cartagena, Colombia where she participated in an art therapy roundtable discussion. Art therapy is a new profession in Colombia and Mrs. Pence's visit aimed to raise awareness about its benefits. She also joined the Vice President for dinner with the President and First Lady of Colombia. The following day, Mrs. Pence visited Calvary Church Cartagena where she led a prayer and met with Venezuelans who had moved to Colombia to escape the Maduro regime. After the visit, she and the Vice President departed for Buenos Aires, Argentina.